# 8. 最後の挨拶

Tsukasa: Are we all ready?!
Nene: Yeah, I'm all set!
Rui: Ready whenever.
Emu: Me too!
Tsukasa: Then, Emu, take it away! Give us an extra dose of energy this time!
Emu: Okay!
Emu: Let's go out there and do our best! Wonderhoy!
Rui, Nene & Tsukasa: Wonderhoy!!!
Alchemist: “At last, it is complete. A robot that can sing in place of our songstress.”
Alchemist: “And here we have a mechanical dragon.”
Troupe Leader, Clown & Songstress: “Whoa!”
Songstress: “Wh-What do I do...?! I can't control the robot...!”
Troupe Leader: “What the—?!”
Alchemist: “Your dream of becoming a star... You simply wish to be seen as one by others, no? To be showered with praise...”
Troupe Leader: “It's true that it's my dream to become a star. A star who brings joy to everyone!”
Troupe Leader: “To me, a star is someone who delights the audience as much as his fellow performers with the most wonderful shows!”
Clown: “I figured out what my dream is.”
Clown: “My dream is to fill the village where we met with smiles and laughter.”
Clown: “So, for now, I guess this is...”
???: “Not so fast!”
Clown: “Huh?”
Miku: <Huh? Something's different.>
MEIKO: <Yes, could it be...? Did they change the ending like we did for our performance?>
Rin: <Cool☆ What do you think their ending's gonna be like?>
KAITO: <I'm looking forward to seeing what they came up with. In any case, I'm sure it'll be...>
???: “Honestly, why is it that none of you thought to discuss this matter with me, the village elder's daughter...?”
Village Elder's Daughter: “What you've all done has without question made this village a much happier place compared to before.”
Village Elder's Daughter: “However, I also believe that we'll have no trouble maintaining the joy you've bestowed upon us.”
Village Elder's Daughter: “On top of that, I'm sure seeing what the world outside of here has to offer will only be to your benefit.”
Village Elder's Daughter: “So, all of you should go! Together!”
Village Elder's Daughter: “And bring that same joy to everyone around the world!”
Clown: “Okay...! Thank you!!!”
MEIKO: <Wow, could things have ended on a happier note?>
Rin: <Hehe♪ I really love this ending☆>
Luka: <Me too. Everyone seems overcome with joy.>
Len: <Yeah, I'm glad they went with this version...!>
Miku: <Me too! And they have such big smiles on their faces!>
Robo-Nene: “And so...”
Robo-Nene: “They made shows together while pursuing their dreams forever after.”
Robo-Nene: “The end!”
Girl: Grandpa, that was so amazing!
Emu: Huh...?
Girl: I didn't know shows could be this much fun! The story was really exciting, and everyone's smiling from ear to ear...!
Grandfather: Hehe. See what I mean? I'm so glad we could come today.
Girl: Hehe. You're smiling too, Grandpa!
Emu: (Everyone has such big smiles on their faces...)
Emu: (The way they're sparkling's so beautiful...)
Emu: (After Grandpa passed away... Everyone stopped coming to the Wonder Stage.)
Emu: (But now...)
Children: Remember when the dragon roared?! That was so cool!
Children: I know, right?! I wanna see that again! Just one more time!
Emu: (I wanna fill this park with even more smiles...)
Emu: (I'm gonna go out into the world with everyone, learn as much as I can, come back here and put smiles on the faces of all our visitors.)
Emu: (And someday... I'm gonna make everyone around the world smile from ear to ear!)
Tsukasa: We greatly appreciate you all joining us today, and for all the support you've given us until now.
Tsukasa: From the bottom of our hearts, thank you very much!!!
Nene, Emu & Rui: Thank you very much!!!
Tsukasa: Well, that's it. Our final showing's over...
Nene: Yeah...
Nene: Even after they found out we'll be leaving soon, our visitors were willing to give us a nice send-off... That made me really happy.
Rui: Yes. I wasn't expecting to receive so many well-wishes.
Emu: Yeah! Oh, that reminds me! Sakurako said, “Make the most of this opportunity like your lives depend on it!”
Nene: Oh, right. She probably had to go back to her own show. It's amazing how she was there for us right up until the end.
Rui: Not only that, our friends from the other stages, including the Phoenix Stage, agreed to put on shows here in our stead. We'll need to thank them again when we get the chance...
Emu: Yeah!
Hinata: Nice work, everyone! Your final performance was so wonderful!
Emu: Oh...! Sis! Keisuke! Shosuke!
Rui: This day wouldn't have been possible without your help. Thank you all very much.
Shosuke: Still, things aren't going to feel quite the same after you've all left the park...
Hinata: Hehe. Are you sure you're okay? We know you're a bit of a crybaby.
Shosuke: Hey, do you really need to mention that now?
Shosuke: Now, more importantly... We have a farewell gift for all of you.
Nene: A farewell gift?
Shosuke: Yes. Remember what we said about getting ourselves introduced to the world of show business?
Shosuke: During our travels, we met all sorts of actors and directors. So, I decided to reach out to some of them to see if there are any troupes or companies out there that'd be willing to help you.
Tsukasa: What?! You did...?!
Shosuke: Yes. Three names came up, and they all differ drastically from one another. I'm sure you'll learn a lot from them.
Nene: You went to all that trouble just for us...?
Shosuke: Well, I'm only going to tell you how to get in touch with them. It'll be on you to actually contact them.
Tsukasa: Thank you very much!
Nene: I... I need to thank you as well!
Shosuke: It was nothing. There's no need to thank me.
Shosuke: I mean, I also want to see what happens after you've been given a chance to really grow.
Emu: Thank you so much, Shosuke!
Tsukasa: Now... Before we leave, I believe it's time for us to make our special salute.
Nene: Yeah, let's do that.
Keisuke: A special salute?
Rui: Yes. We'd like to take this opportunity to say goodbye to our most valued companion.
Emu: Alright, Tsukasa, take it away!
Tsukasa: Okay.
Tsukasa: This is our final salute... To the Wonder Stage.
Tsukasa: You were the reason we were able to have as much fun as we did!
Tsukasa: Thank you for all that you've given us until now!!!
Rui, Emu & Nene: Thank you!!!
Emu: (The Wonder Stage spent this entire time watching over us as we pursued our dreams...)
Emu: (Grandpa's dream, my dream and everyone else's dreams...)
Emu: (Thank you from the bottom of my heart.)
Emu: (I promise to come back after I've learned how to fill this park with even more smiles. So...)
Emu: I'll see you again!!!
Tsukasa: Allriiight!!
Tsukasa: It's time for the curtain to rise on the next chapter of Wonderlands×Showtime's epic tale!!!
Nene: Didn't you say something like this before...?
Rui: Hehe. I'm looking forward to seeing how this next chapter turns out.
Emu: I don't know what's gonna happen...
Emu: But I'm really excited...! And feel super wonderhoy!
Tsukasa: Yes, I as well!
Tsukasa: So! Let's take these feelings and get ready to weigh anchor!!!
Emu: Here we go, you guys! We're setting sail for our dreams! Won-won...
Emu, Tsukasa, Nene & Rui: Wonderhoy!!!
Emu, Tsukasa, Nene & Rui: Haha! Hahaha! Hehe...
